metaData.descriptionCS: The examinee points to one of three words with a similar meaning as the target work or reads a sentence and selects the word that has a similar meaning as the target word.

questions.title: †Item 1. house (home)
questions.correctInstructionsHTML:
Correct response [home]:

That’s right. Home (point) can mean the same as house (point), so the answer is home.
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect or no response:

Home (point) can mean the same as house (point), so the answer is home. Teach further as needed and then say, Let’s try another one.
questions.topInstructionsHTML:
Now I will ask you to read some words.

This word (point to the word house) tells about this picture (point). The word is house (point).

One of these words (point to the three words below the house) can also mean house (point to the word house). The words are: door, home, ride (point to each word). Which one of these words can mean house? (Pause for response.)

questions.title: †Item 2. see (look)
questions.correctInstructionsHTML:
Correct response [look]:

That's right. The answer is look because look (point) can mean the same as see (point).
questions.incorrectInstructionsHTML:
Incorrect or no response:

The answer is look because look (point) can mean the same as see (point). Teach further as needed and then say, Let’s try another one.
questions.topInstructionsHTML:
Here is the next one.

This word (point to see) tells about this picture (point). The word is see (point).

One of these words (point to the three words below the boy) can also mean the same as see (point to see). The words are step, feet, look (point to each word). Which one of these words can mean see? (Pause for response.)

questions.title: Sample A. over (above)
questions.topInstructionsHTML:
Now I will ask you to read some sentences.

Point to the item and say, Let’s do the first one together. The question is, Which word means over? The bird flew above the roof. Which word in this sentence can mean over? (Pause for response.) Above (point) can mean the same as over (point), so the answer is above.

questions.title: Sample B. cold (icy)
questions.topInstructionsHTML:
Let’s try another one. The question is, Which word means cold? Her drink was icy and sweet. Which word in this sentence can mean cold? (Pause for response.) The answer is icy because icy (point) can mean the same as cold (point).

When I show you the next screen, you will see more sentences. Read each question and sentence carefully, and then say or point to the answer.

Do you have any questions? (Pause for response.) Teach further as needed, and then continue to the next screen.
